<paragraph blockId="25.[136,1452,698,905]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
Widespread in the West Indies and northern South America (
<collectingCountry box="[879,994,734,760]" name="Colombia" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1006,1124,734,760]" name="Venezuela" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1136,1231,734,760]" name="Ecuador" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1243,1314,734,760]" name="Brazil" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1327,1440,734,761]" name="Suriname" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Suriname</collectingCountry>
); new to Central America.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[136,1452,698,905]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
The specimen is corresponding to 
<taxonomicName box="[545,656,806,832]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Radulaceae" genus="Radula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="fendleri">
<emphasis box="[545,656,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">R. fendleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
according to the key presented by 
<bibRefCitation author="Yamada, K." box="[1011,1228,806,832]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" pagination="379 - 390" refId="ref26593" refString="Yamada, K. (1988) The genus Radula from Cuba. Journal of the Hattori Botanical Laboratory 65: 379 - 390." type="journal article" year="1988">Yamada (1988: 383)</bibRefCitation>
, not to 
<taxonomicName authority="Steph." authorityName="Steph." class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Oryzolejeunea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="saccatiloba">
<emphasis box="[1300,1452,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">R. saccatiloba</emphasis>
Steph.
</taxonomicName>
which was considered synonymous with 
<taxonomicName box="[663,778,842,868]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Radulaceae" genus="Radula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="fendleri">
<emphasis box="[663,778,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">R. fendleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gradstein, S. R. &amp; Hekking, W. H. A." box="[822,1140,842,868]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" pagination="197 - 230" refId="ref22060" refString="Gradstein, S. R. &amp; Hekking, W. H. A. (1989) A catalogue of the Bryophytes of the Guianas. I. Hepaticae and Anthocerotae. Journal of the Hattori Botanical Laboratory 66: 197 - 230." type="journal article" year="1989">Gradstein &amp; Hekking (1989)</bibRefCitation>
. In a recent molecular study (
<bibRefCitation author="Devos, N. &amp; Renner, M. A. M. &amp; Gradstein, S. R. &amp; Shaw, J. &amp; Vanderpoorten, A." box="[143,332,878,905]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" pagination="1623 - 1632" refId="ref21378" refString="Devos, N., Renner, M. A. M., Gradstein, S. R., Shaw, J. &amp; Vanderpoorten, A. (2011) Molecular data challenge traditional subgeneric divisions in the leafy liverwort Radula. Taxon 60: 1623 - 1632." type="journal article" year="2011">Devos et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
) these two species were nested in different clades and were assigned to two different subgenera.
</paragraph>
